	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>1) Low health/frenzy aggro &gt; all.<br />
<br />
If by sitting a caster gains aggro, yes, the mob will probably shift its aggro back to the tank when the caster stands back up.<br />
<br />
2) Yes, theoretically you can pingpong aggro like that but...<br />
<br />
3) ...afaik a pet's taunt skill kinda sucks, most of its aggro is generated through pure DPS &amp; procs.<br />
<br />
4) It can be, if you have a skilled paladin/SK who will help out with root/FD &amp; proximity. Your cleric will be healing two tanks instead of one if you rely on just taunt. Also it depends on how quickly you can gain aggro and how quickly the mobs die, it's inefficient if mobs are halfway dead when you gain aggro.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
