	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Most of your questions have already been answered pretty well. Just in relation to your last question, in  my experience, riding on knights does help a lot, as long as both know what they are doing.  <br />
<br />
first off, i tend to find this works better with pallys than SKs.  Let the pally stun on inc, tank till slow lands. Normally with just a single stun they can hold aggro through slow. Once slow lands, taunt off them.  Its really that simple. All the pally has to do is to show restraint and not try to steal aggro back once u have it.<br />
<br />
However, before u even consider this, you have to weigh up the advantages - i.e. only if you have a reasonably significant AC/HP advantage. This is because the cleric is going to have to heal pally and heal you each fight and if you arent offering enough advantages to offset the cleric having to heal both, then its not worth it and better to just let the pally MA.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
