</span> </div>
				<div class="info">Join Date: Apr 2003</div>
				
				<div class="info">Guild: <a href="http://www.rageveeshan.com">Rage Veeshan</a></div>
				<div class="info">Server: Veeshan</a></div>
				
				 
				<div class="info">Posts: 826 
				</div>
				<div class="info">   </div>
				</div>														
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Beastlords have a line of buffs that add a proc to their pet (also adds 75dex as well), these procs not only do pretty mean amount of damage, but many of these procs carry a +hate modifier, allowing the pet to hold agro through the BSTs slows.<br />
<br />
Easy way to gain agro...let the pet attack while only the warrior is in range.  The pet can't taunt off the warrior while he's close, and it &quot;helps&quot; you gain agro, since it's holding agro over the slow also (as well as doing damage).  I'm surprised more people don't do this...<br />
<br />
4) This is also known as &quot;piggybacking&quot;...many SKs use this method since we can lose the agro after warriors have taunted off, allowing us to use our spells again to do damage without fear of over-agroing.  Don't know about paladins tho.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				&quot;I tried being reasonable. You all saw me. I have no other recourse but to shove him into the lava.&quot; <br />
~ Black Mage, 8-Bit Theater
			</div>
		<!-- / sig -->
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
